Weekly Happenings are here! For those of you new to our district, our goal is to publish a weekly "happenings" of the events, announcements, and useful information for our families.

We send this via email blast and on our district website. If you would like to be added to the email blast, please email kburger8@kelsoc-7.k12.mo.us with your request to be added.

Added note: In the morning, if the cars are wrapped around the outer lane of the parking lot onto the highway, please come into the center isle and even park if needed. When the highway is blocked it puts our families in the line of traffic and more importantly, unsafe. Please help us in the mornings by coming into the center isle if the outer lane is full. Thanks!

post_text:
Moving into 2020-21: Athletics

Let's begin with the premise, that there are still a lot of unknowns of COVD-19. The goal has and is always to do what's best for kids. Kelso C-7 will follow both CDC and MSHAA guidance for athletic safety.

âœ…All athletes must have a sports' physical every 2 years. (Note this has changed from the previous yearly requirement.)

âœ…Before athletes are allowed to practice, families must have a complete physical form. The link for the form to take with you to the doctor can be found on the district's homepage, listed as "Physical Form."

âœ… Grades 5-8: Help us plan for next year by letting us know your family's participation plan. Below is a survey link to let us know what students will be playing sports next year. We will examine the numbers fielded and make a decision on 4th grade participation for programs.

We are hosting a a whole week of THANK YOU's to all who helped make sure our students were well cared for during the COVID-19 closure. As always our school is blessed by so many!

Today we thank all of our Kelso C-7 employees! As always, in adversity they not only rose the challenge, but rocked it! They hosted zoom parties and classes, taught from their showers and yards, visited (at a safe social distance) kids houses, delivered meals and homework, and showed our kids that even when its scary, Falcons rise to the challenge and they truly exemplified what it is to be #FalconStrong.

Thank you all!

post_text:
We are hosting a whole week of THANK YOU's to all who helped make sure our students were well cared for during the COVID-19 closure. As always our school is blessed by so many!

We are starting with our community! Our people never fail to come through for our students!
-NBC Fire Department (pictured) was there with us, making sure that student meals were prepared, packaged and ready for delivery!
-Dollar General of Scott City and Bob's Food Liner of Scott City donated plastic bags for food delivery and student item pick up. Something so simple was a huge help!
-Father Casteel, Father Bala, Frank Glueck, and Jesus In Disguise Food Pantry who met with us from the beginning to plan for our community during this crazy time! To see all come together with so much love and compassion for our community is truly a blessing!
-Community member who made monetary donations for families and services during COVID-19.
-All who helped us celebrate our graduates in the parking lot and lined the streets with signs and cheers during the parade.

post_text:
Unfortunately, ladies and gentlemen this makes it official. Kelso C7 will not meet in person for the remainder of the year. This is extremely sad to know we have to wait so long to see our kids in the hallways again.

Our faculty and staff were holding out hope that we would return, however, we were also prepared in case we did not return. A mass letter was mailed to our families today that outlines our long-term learning plan.

We will continue to push through this adversity and anxiously wait until our family returns to school.

Stay well Kelso C7 and be #FalconStrong!

ğŸ’™ğŸ’›ğŸ’™

Governor Mike Parson
April 9 at 2:56 PM Â·

We are ordering all Missouri public and charter schools to remain closed through the remainder of the academic year with the exceptions of nutrition services and child care that are outlined in our recent health order.

This recommendation was made by working together with the Missouri Department of Elementary and Secondary Education and several school superintendents from across the state -- from both urban and rural districts.

Schools should continue remote learning for their students until the end date previously set on their academic calendars.

Happy first day of Spring Break!! I know that the idea of spring break is kind of tongue and cheek, but we believe that a break from assignments being posted and challenges is what is needed for our school family under our circumstances.

We hope that our families enjoy the additional time that has been gifted to us, have some fun in the sun, feel the safety of your homes, learn some basic life skills, and, if needed, catch up on any learning/assignments.

Our food distribution will continue this week on Monday, Wednesday, and Thursday.

We will be back at it on Monday, April 13th. Enjoy some sunshine and our blessings Kelso C-7 Family! Happy Easter all!

post_text:
Dear Parents, Faculty, and Community Members,

The Scott-Mississippi County Area School Superintendents have met and made the decision to extend the school closure up to and including April 13th. For Kelso C-7 School, there is no change of dates from the previous communications. Classes will resume on April 14th. This decision will be re-evaluated on April 6th. At this time, districts across the state are continually evaluating the situation, taking the advice of state and local health departments, as well as the CDC, to make informed and careful decisions. Our main concern is the health and well-being of our students and their families.

We will continue to provide breakfast and lunch to our families during this extended closure on Mondays (2 meals), Wednesday (2 meals), and Fridays (1 meal). Please continue to monitor communications through our emails, our Facebook page, and our website.

Sincerely,

Dr. Kimberly Burger
Superintendent of Schools
Kelso C-7 School District

Update: The Preschool Enrollment night has been postponed to TBD date. Mrs. Bentley will be reaching out to families with more details.

Dear Kelso C-7 Families,

Our district is currently suffering from an outbreak of sickness. We have confirmed cases of Type B flu, stomach bugs, and cold/sinus issues. With that in mind, Kelso C-7 will be closed for Wednesday, February 12th and closed for Parent-Teacher Conferences on Thursday, February 13th. School will resume on Tuesday, February 18th as planned. Parties will be made up on Tuesday, February 18th when students return to school. First gradeâ€™s party will be Wednesday, February 19th due to a prearranged teacher absence. Parent-Teacher Conferences will be made up via phone calls, appointments, or other arrangements between parents and individual teachers.
As of now, the district will not have to make up this day due to hours built into the calendar.
Thanks for your understanding as we try to keep our school family well!
Dr. Kim Burger
